<h4 class="title">Curriculum and Course Structure of MD/MS Programs in Nepal</h4>
<p>
Nepal's MD/MS curricula are comparable to the Indian one, with minor topic and course structure differences. Nepal's combined MD/MS programs may be completed in three to five years, with the exact time spent in school determined by the student's chosen area of focus. The program provides classroom instruction and hands-on experience through clinical rotations and research.
</p>
<p>
Anatomy, physiology, pharmacology, microbiology, pathology, and community medicine are just a few topics covered in the curriculum. General Surgery, Internal Medicine, Pediatrics, Obstetrics and Gynecology, Orthopedics, Radiology, and Ophthalmology are only a few specialties offered by MD/MS schools in Nepal.
</p>
<p>
Besides the standard curriculum, MD/MS programs in Nepal emphasize soft skills training, such as public speaking, teamwork, and professional ethics. Earning a medical degree in Nepal opens doors to various subspecialties and a rigorous curriculum that sets students up for success in the medical sector.
</p>
</div>

<div class="content-post">
    <h4 class="title">Career Prospects and Opportunities after MD/MS in Nepal</h4>
<p>
Know your options after earning your MD/MS degree in Nepal. A medical doctor or medical scientist with a master's degree in Nepal has several options for additional education and specialization.
</p>
<p>
Graduates of medical schools in Nepal have a good chance of finding a job in public and private clinics, hospitals, and universities. Cardiology, neurology, and oncology are just a few specialties in great demand.
</p>
